args: Found somethin', {player_name}!\nYesss! A mushroom! Food at last!
That will be delicious whether we boil or\ngrill it. What do you think we should do?
Eh, both are too much hassle. Let's just eat\nit before you-know-who comes along\nand steals it from...
Gya! You-know-who is HERE!\nShe on our right or our left?!
Ha ha! I'm in the TREES!
Oh no! She got our mushroom!
AAAH HA HA! Such is the way of nature!\nThe strong take from the weak, and the\nweak go mushroom-less!
Dammit! She's gone! How long is this crap\ngonna go on for, anyways?!\n
Out all night AGAIN, Ranzal?\nWhy do you never learn?
And you, {player_name}! Even if\nyou are tempted to go out and enjoy the\nnight life, you must learn to say no!
Aw, quit naggin' so much. Ain't nothin'\nwrong with some male-bondin' time.
I mean, a little more freedom ain't a\nbad thing, ya know?
You don't regret what you've done one bit!\n...And you know what? I've got just the\nthing for that.
I know somebody who will shape up this\nlifestyle of yours. ...MASTER!
SHE DOES MEAN, FOR IT IS I!
Cleo has recently confided in me that\nSOME people in the castle have been\nmaking a mockery of common decency.
I've decided to draft up new rules and\nregulations so as to do something about\nthe deplorable standards of conduct here.
Rules?! Regulations?! Are ya kiddin' me?!
Rule Number One: Wake with the sunrise!\nRule Number Two: Bed immediately after\ndinner!
And Rule Number Three: Evening curfew!\nOnce curfew is in effect, going out is\nEXPRESSLY forbidden!
I will be meting out swift—AND harsh—\npunishment to any found in violation of\nthese new rules. Is this understood?
WAKE UP, WAKE UP, WAAAAKE UP!\nYou have three seconds to leave your bed!\n...Three! ...Two! ...One!
Blargh! What are you doing in my room,\nCelliera?!
The sun has risen, which means it's time\nto get up. And if you're half-asleep,\nI'll glue your eyes open!
I'm up! I'm up! Leave my eyes alone!
Whoa. That's a hell of a hand,\n{player_name}.
A-HEM! It is FAR past lights-out time.\nNow get back to your rooms, and make it\nsnappy!
Oh, and if you can't sleep, I'll sing you a\nlittle ditty I call ＂A Lullaby from Hell.＂
All right, all right! We hear ya.
*sigh* We ain't havin' fun at all ever since\nCelliera took over.
Although we ARE living healthier lifestyles.
Sure, but who wants to live a longer life\nin a prison like this? Not this guy!
I guess it does feel a little restrictive.
Right? That's why I got a plan.\nNow listen here...  *whisper* *whisper*
Ha ha! Slipped out like a pair'a pros,\nam I right?!
There's plenty of taverns open late.\nWe'll tear it up at one of 'em tonight!
Er, but it's REALLY late, Ranzal.\nAre you sure this is a good idea?
'Course it is. But what AIN'T a good idea\nis clappin' us in irons with a buncha lame\nrules what restrict our basic freedoms!
We're free men, so let's roll like it already!
We gotta hurry back to our rooms before\nanyone notices.
I admire your guts—but that's ALL I\nadmire of this pathetic little plan.
This, uh, ain't what it looks like! We were\njust going to the, uh, thing! For the, er...\nY'know? The...thing?
Your excuses are futile! You have broken\nthe rules, and must be PUNISHED!
If it is freedom you desire so badly...\nthen freedom you shall HAVE!
...Can't believe her punishment was to\nforce us into the woods for a buncha\n ＂self-sufficiency＂ trainin'.
Well, we ARE free to choose when to go\nto bed and what to eat...
I'm so hungry, my head's spinning.\nIf only I could've eaten that mushroom...\nUrgghh...
Dammit! First she yammers on about\n＂survival of the fittest,＂ and now she's\nstealin' all our food!
WE AIN'T GONNA TAKE IT NO MORE!
Guuuh... Shoutin' made my head spin...\nHuurgh...
Well? You've had your taste of freedom.\nThoughts? General impressions?
Excelsior! You've learned quite a lesson.
Now relax. I'm not some kind of demon.\nI understand full well that everyone has\nto have SOME fun now and then.
So if you'll practice punctuality and\nmoderation, I will relax the rules. ...A bit!
Now that THAT'S sorted, let's beat feet\nback to the castle, yeah?
Oh, one has nothing to do with the other.\nA punishment is a punishment!
You have three days of training to go,\nand it WILL continue!
